    {
        "content": "<p><code>rw</code> does not see through <code>abbrev</code>s in the same way that <code>simp</code> does</p>",
        "id": 571062353,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769787766
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ohje</p>",
        "id": 571062452,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769787794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a good reason for this?</p>",
        "id": 571062550,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769787825
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>from <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Lean.Meta.kabstract#doc\">docs#Lean.Meta.kabstract</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We detect subterms equivalent to p using key-matching. That is, only perform isDefEq tests when the head symbol of subterm is equivalent to head symbol of p.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 571062601,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769787837
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this is an optimization so we don't have to check every subterm</p>",
        "id": 571062750,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769787873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anything i can do to make my abbrev extra-see-through?</p>",
        "id": 571062913,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769787919
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>unfortunately it is the head symbol here</p>",
        "id": 571062950,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769787929
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and will always be</p>",
        "id": 571062987,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769787941
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could do a <code>notation</code></p>",
        "id": 571063098,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769787965
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And then a custom delaborator again, so that it doesn't always show up, but only if there is possbile ambiguity in the context? i.e. two elements of type <code>Interpretation _</code></p>",
        "id": 571063547,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz R",
        "timestamp": 1769788073
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>see for example the notation for <code>IsOpen</code> that makes the topology explicit, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Topology.IsOpen_of#doc\">docs#Topology.IsOpen_of</a></p>",
